1978;;Born Again;;American;;Irving Rapper;;Dean Jones, Anne Francis, Dana Andrews;;unknown;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Born_Again_(film);;As President Richard Nixon's Special Counsel, Colson had his own office in the White House, power and prestige. After Watergate he had a prison record… and a strong faith. Colson, played by Dean Jones, pleads guilty to Watergate-related charges and is sent to prison. The experience leaves him radically changed, and he decides to establish Prison Fellowship – a ministry that now reaches around the world.[1]